description.originalText: Madalyn is an exceptional worker. We enjoyed having her a part of our family. My daughter connected well with Madalyn. She helped my daughter with her speech and taught her some Spanish.

Maddie took care of three of our children 2, 6 and 10 on our weeklong trip to New York. She was warm and caring especially with my clingy two year old. I did not worry at all leaving them with her. Maddie took my six year old to the children’s museum and pretended with him. I appreciated how she stayed engaged. She was also flexible and agreeable even when our plans altered and she had to meet us at a different place. Maddie always smiled and had an infectious laugh. She stayed positive even when my kids were cranky. My kids loved her. Finally, she was able to help tidy up or hotel room. That was a bonus! I would definitely recommend her as a babysitter.

Madalyn was extremely patient with our son. He’s super active and sometimes has random out Burst. So it was nice to see that Maddy took her time with him. She was loving and kept him safe always. She came prepared with games and arts& crafts which was so thoughtful. Thank you again and hope to see you soon.

description.displayText: Maddy is an incredible caregiver-- so warm, enthusiastic, professional, prompt, and reliable. We hired her for a whole month as we searched for a NYC apartment and daycare, and we worried that having a brand-new caregiver would be strange and scary for our 22-month-old. But our little girl took to Maddy almost *immediately*-- within hour Maddy had her giggling while dancing and singing and looking at books. By Day 2, our little one was running to the door with excitement when Maddy came over. Maddy even made her little meals and took her on excursions-- Maddy went to culinary school and is an excellent cook. We couldn't have been happier with Maddy; she made our family's transition to New York so wonderfully smooth. Thank you, Maddy!

description.displayText: Madalyn thank you so much for coming last minute to care for my 1 year old. I had meetings back to back and had to run errands. I asked Madalyn to do what she can as she is expecting a baby of her own. I was very happy to find dinner made without me asking and a clean kitchen after a long day of work. Madalyn also organized my sons clothes which was very helpful has I had some of his summer clothes still out. Madalyn took her time to do all these things while my son napped. Before his nap she worked on letters, numbers and teaching him his colors. She also made a very cool indoor tent with my son and used her imagination to make him feel like they were camping it was the cutest thing ever. Definitely recommend Maddy.

description.displayText: Madalyn was just fabulous. She took very good care of our 4 month old baby girl L and our very active 2 year old son j. Maddy kept us in the loop the whole time with pictures through out the day. I really appreciate the fact that Maddy cleaned and reorganized my messy room/closet. She even left notes about the children to keep me up to date. Maddy was 20 mins early and although it was our first time meeting her my 2 year old just connected with her so fast. I definitely recommend Maddy, you won't regret hiring her.

description.displayText: I hired Madalyn today to care for my 3 year old daughter. She cared for my daughter from 12pm-6pm. Madalyn was very patient and loving to my daughter. She took our daughter out to the park, did some Arts&crafts with her. She also made dinner and bathe her. Madalyn kept us up to date while we were at work. She would notify us when our daughter would use the bathroom as she is learning how to use the potty. Madalyn also cleaned our messy home which we were very thankful for due to our busy schedules we don't really get to clean up. Thank you Madalyn for taking such good care of our daughter she loved you. Hope you see you again soon. We totally recommend Madalyn.
